        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 18 at 1:59PM MDT by NWS Pocatello ID</headline>
        <description>At 157 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a line of strong
thunderstorms extending from 14 miles southwest of Rockland to near
Sublett , moving northeast at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts in excess of 45 mph and nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Eastern Pocatello, McCammon, Inkom, Arimo, Rockland, Fort Hall
Bannock Peak, Portneuf Gap, Pauline, Mink Creek Pass, Hawkins
Reservoir, Arbon, Sublett Reservoir, and Roy.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.

These storms may intensify, so be certain to monitor local radio
stations and available television stations for additional
information and possible warnings from the National Weather Service.</instruction>
